node.text:
Ever wondered WHY it's so hard to STOP doing something,  or why its so DIFFICULT to just SAY NO ..... 

Understand why and HOW and your more likely to be able break that damaging routine, kick that habit .... 

Over coming habits is half the battle when it comes to weight loss, when working with clients, I go deeper that just set plans to follow, I teach you HOW to follow them also. 

to find out more head to www.martynfordcoaching.com VERY limited spaces left.  #transformation #weightgain #fatloss #addiction

node.text:
It has become extremely popular and almost trendy to follow a Vegan or plant based diet...... HOWEVER is this the best choice for YOU and your goals? 

Obviously there are more major determining factors in this thought process for many, such as animal welfare, carbon footprint and so forth. HOWEVER if we are just looking from a health and performance perspective, there are a few factors to consider...

#vegan #plantbased #veganfood #nutrition #fitness #protein

node.title: Plant Based Protein Vs Animal Protein

node.text: My new morning ritual .... its taken me a few years to truly appreciate the importance of RECOVERY, nearly 40 and feeling the best i have EVER felt, speaks volumes.  If you really want to ENJOY life fully, you need to start appreciating what's required to do so. That starts at this time EVERY day.  Take 10 minutes to wake up properly, have a few glasses of water, and a coffee, stretch and pull back that string ready for another productive day.  Be greatful for every day we get, tomorrow isn't promised #rewind #relax #enjoy

node.text:
VEGAN VS MEAT .... 

Those insisting on eating a strictly plant based diets need to consider that the digestibility and essential amino acid content is not the same or as complete as animal protein. Although a plant based diet is possible, extra considerations need to be taken into account and aiming for a higher protein intake is essential as anywhere from 45-80% of amino acids from plant based protein are available in the bloodstream after consumption, in comparison to animal protein at 90% ....
I FREAKING love my job ...... @lukasz_lodziana_ you absolutely smashed it brother 🙌👏💪

node.text: After months and months of not been able to train shoulders, finally I have some ROM back, all I'm currently doing is light weights and manipulation of the muscles with pre exhaust sets and TUT, not only is the joint getting stronger and stability coming back, muscle growth is starting to occur once more.  I cant stress enough the need to look after your joints and muscles as you age.  By all means train with insane intensity and like an animal BUT be sensible and understand when and how to apply that mind set.  Just because your not using the biggest weights in the gym,  doesn't mean your not working the muscle hard.  Learn to feel the movement and engage the muscles.  Train smart, train hard and enjoy the process ....

node.text: DONT BE AN ADAM .... listen to your coach .... ADAM didn't, and he didn't get 10 reps ... Rep ranges are important to understand, especially if you want to really progress and grow some muscle. (PS no Adams were hurt during the making of this)
